{"ID":270356, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"356\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs355.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs357.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 356<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Our Greatest Responsibility<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">What promises are made in relation to the subject of the salvation of the dead?<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> and what kind\n  of characters are those who can be saved, although their bodies are mouldering and decaying in the\n  grave? When his commandments teach us, it is in view of eternity; for we are looked upon by God<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span>\n  as though we were in eternity. God dwells in eternity,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> and does not view things as we do.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The greatest responsibility in this world that God has laid upon us is to seek after our dead. The\n  Apostle says, &ldquo;They without us cannot be made perfect;&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> (Hebrews 11:40)<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> for it is necessary that\n  the sealing power<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> should be in our hands to seal our children and our dead<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> for the fulness of the\n  dispensation of times<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span>&mdash;a dispensation to meet the promises made by Jesus Christ before the\n  foundation of the world<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> for the salvation of man.<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Now, I will speak of them. I will meet Paul half way. I say to you, Paul, you cannot be perfect\n  without us.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> It is necessary that those who are going before and those who come after us should\n  have salvation in common<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> with us; and thus hath God made it obligatory upon man. Hence, God\n  said, &ldquo;I will send you Elijah the prophet before the coming of the great and dreadful day of the Lord;\n  and he shall turn the heart of the fathers to the children, and the heart of the children to their fathers,\n  lest I come and smite the earth with a curse.&rdquo; (Malachi 4:5-6.)<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">A Salvation for Men<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">I have a declaration to make as to the provisions which God hath made to suit the conditions\n  of man<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span>&mdash;made from before the foundation of the world.<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> What has Jesus said? All sin, and all\n  blasphemies, and every transgression, except one, that man can be guilty of, may be forgiven;<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and\n  there is a salvation for all men, either in this world or the world to come,<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> who have not committed\n  the unpardonable sin,<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> there being a pro-<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116106\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116106)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116106)\">D&amp;C 128:5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115740\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115740)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115740)\">D&amp;C 121:2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110563\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110563)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110563)\">2 Pet. 3:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114805\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114805)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114805)\">D&amp;C 88:13<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116890\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116890)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116890)\">Moses 7:31,35<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117018\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117018)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117018)\">Abr. 3:4<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117177\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117177)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117177)\">JS&mdash;H 1 Endnote<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107246\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107246)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107246)\">Isa. 55:8-9<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116160\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116160)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116160)\">D&amp;C 128:15,18<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110296\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110296)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110296)\">Heb. 11:40<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114310\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114310)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114310)\">D&amp;C 68:12<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116153\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116153)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116153)\">D&amp;C 128:14<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116301\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116301)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116301)\">D&amp;C 131:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116431\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116431)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116431)\">D&amp;C 132:46<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116689\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116689)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116689)\">D&amp;C 138:48<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109774\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109774)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109774)\">Eph. 1:10<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115989\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115989)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115989)\">D&amp;C 124:41<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116175\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116175)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116175)\">D&amp;C 128:18<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">10. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110958\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110958)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110958)\">1 Ne. 10:18<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111184\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111184)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111184)\">2 Ne. 9:18<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111550\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111550)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111550)\">Mosiah 4:6-7<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111919\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111919)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111919)\">Alma 12:25,30<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112318\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112318)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112318)\">Alma 42:26<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112690\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112690)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112690)\">3 Ne. 26:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112855\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112855)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112855)\">Ether 3:14<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115963\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115963)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115963)\">D&amp;C 124:33<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116109\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116109)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116109)\">D&amp;C 128:5,8,22<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">11. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111636\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111636)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111636)\">Mosiah 15:24<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">12. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110297\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110297)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110297)\">Heb. 11:40<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">13. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110639\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110639)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110639)\">Jude 1:3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">14. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107752\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107752)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107752)\">Mal. 4:5-6<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">15. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110298\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110298)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110298)\">Heb. 11:40<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">16. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116909\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116909)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116909)\">Moses 7:47<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">17. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107968\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107968)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107968)\">Matt. 12:31-32<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">18. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108357\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108357)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108357)\">Mark 10:30<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110191\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110191)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110191)\">Heb. 6:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114126\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114126)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114126)\">D&amp;C 59:23<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116844\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116844)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116844)\">Moses 6:59<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">19. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112248\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112248)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112248)\">Alma 39:6<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n  <div class=\"textFootnotes\">\n    \n      <p class=\"cont\">tion of his being a fallen prophet could be made. The Prophet lived his life in <i>crescendo.<\/i> From small beginnings, it rose in breadth and power as he neared its close. As a teacher he reached the climax of his career in this discourse. After it there was but one thing more he could do&mdash;seal his testimony with his blood. This he did less than three months later. Such is not the manner of life of false prophets.&mdash;Note by Elder B. H. Roberts.<\/p>\n    \n  <\/div>\n<\/div>"}